snippet.textDisplay:
Kaiser, I love you. I the staff. Your facial expression, your holding back of tears. I will forever support you all. I just wish I made enough money to pay my bills, and pay you guys because you deserve the world.

You guys literally made the last 7 years of my life less hectic than it was by giving me the laughs to combat my depression and social issues. I use all of you guys work in my daily life and make references to you guys jokes because you guys are what essentially raised me after I forgot who i was.

That might not sound good but honestly. I love you guys. I wouldn’t change anything and I swear to god I’ll get a better job and work harder to help you guys out too!

snippet.textDisplay: I’m so disappointed in you guys you released episodes to the fan base slower and slower to the point where it would take a year for an episode. Now you’re outright telling us that you won’t be delivering on what you’ve promised. You’ve turned your back on the brand and you’ve turned your passion into a business model and ruined it all. I’ve been around since season one first came out and I’ve seen the way you guys grew but you’ve absolutely failed me in terms of communication. It is clear you guys do not care about the fans and it is very sad and disappointing to see that you guys feel like you can just pick up and drop projects whenever you feel like no matter how people feel about the work you put out. It’s sad you guys have made this because your channel will not survive without DBZA and I know once you realize that you’ll pick it back up again.
